00:09:29,529 --> 00:09:33,580
is just not there and the way that it was
four years ago.

183
00:09:33,580 --> 00:09:35,529
Part of that is due to how these smaller parties
have performed.

184
00:09:35,529 --> 00:09:39,520
But a larger part is how the DPP has performed
the last four years.

185
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:44,380
So the DPP has had a majority in Taiwan's
legislature,

186
00:09:44,380 --> 00:09:45,880
they've had the presidency,

187
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:49,000
but a lot of their policies have kind of been
very lukewarm.

188
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,170
People aren't really excited about

189
00:09:50,170 --> 00:09:51,850
how they've performed the last four years

190
00:09:51,850 --> 00:09:55,080
and that's hurt their popularity.

191
00:09:55,080 --> 00:10:01,050
So this year people are kind of just much
more scared that the KMT

192
00:10:01,050 --> 00:10:03,610
will actually do well.

193
00:10:03,610 --> 00:10:07,750
And four years ago people kind of knew they
weren't going to do well,

194
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:10,460
which kind of creates this bigger sense of
dread

195
00:10:10,460 --> 00:10:12,839
around the future of Taiwanese politics.

196
00:10:12,839 --> 00:10:14,760
There's a very popular phrase in Mandarin

197
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:18,290
that's been going around called "Wang guo
gan", meaning,

