00:10:42,390 --> 00:10:44,910
So the best example is that

206
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:48,710
they switched out their presidential candidate

207
00:10:48,710 --> 00:10:50,380
two months before the election.

208
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:51,880
That's bad.

209
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:54,430
That was bad, because it showed one

210
00:10:54,430 --> 00:10:57,960
a total lack of support in their candidate.

211
00:10:57,960 --> 00:11:00,560
It kind of seemed that they were kind of throwing
in the towel

212
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:01,780
two months early.

213
00:11:01,780 --> 00:11:03,990
They switched as a kind of a hail Mary way
to kind of

214
00:11:03,990 --> 00:11:08,340
consolidate support within the party.

215
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:10,860
Not only that, but Ma Ying-jeou was not a
particularly

216
00:11:10,860 --> 00:11:13,660
strong president in his later years

217
00:11:13,660 --> 00:11:16,690
that a lot of people were just generally unhappy
with the KMT.

218
00:11:16,690 --> 00:11:18,740
So a lot of people either didn't vote last...

219
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:21,350
A lot of KMT supporters here, they didn't
vote last election

